  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing public participation and demand for accountability in local governance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.One-day National Stakeholders&#x2019; Forum on Media and Accountable Local Governance in Ghana. 
2.Eight district-level stakeholder meetings 
3.Development of Media/Communication strategies for target MMDAs 
4.Training for MMDA officials on effective utilisation of the media and communication strategy 
5.Quarterly separate district-level Live Broadcast Governance Forums. Production/broadcast of quarterly &#x201C;State of District&#x201D; radio     programmes
6.Half yearly production and printing of policy briefs and research materials</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project will form part of the MFWA&#x2019;s wider Media and Governance Programme interventions, which seek to strengthen capacity of the media to be effective enablers of participatory, transparent and accountable governance in West Africa. Specifically, this proposed project will build on the initiatives started last year in the proposed eight MMDAs in the Upper West Region (Sissala East Municipal, Wa Municipal, Wa East district, Wa West district and Lawra Municipal), Northern region (West Mamprusi district) Central region (Twifo Atti-Morkwa district) and Western region (Ellembelle district). 
 The choice of the target districts is to strengthen the citizens-authorities&#x2019; governance dialogue engagement platforms created in the districts to increase the yields in the area of citizens&#x2019; access to information and authorities&#x2019; responsiveness. Already, the District Facebook pages created are beginning to gather organic likes and followers and must be supported to continue.</narrative>
  </description>
